    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03721.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden NJ<ptr target="loc.03721_n2"/></name>
                    <date when="1885-05-12"><hi rend="underline">5th 12th 85</hi></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman Esq</salute>
                <salute>Dear Walt:</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I <hi rend="underline">fear</hi> you
                   do not
                 fully appreciate my relations to the Springfield <choice><orig>Repub</orig><reg>Republican</reg></choice>-people <hi rend="underline">anent</hi> the W.
                W article.<ptr target="loc.05890_n1"/></p>
            <p>There has been a good deal of writing about it, between them &#38; me&#8212;and
                about two weeks ago I sent on
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03721.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/> a <hi
                    rend="underline">red-hot</hi> interview of my own with H W Beecher.<ptr
                    target="n0066"/> Well: they didn't "bite" at the HWB-MSS&#8212;it was a trifle
                too <hi rend="underline">warm</hi> &amp; cut both ways Blaine-&#38;anti-Blaine<ptr
                    target="loc.03721_n3"/>                <hi rend="underline">but</hi> the managing editor quietly says "We are still
                waiting for that long-promised article on Walt Whitman"&#8212;</p>
            <p>I <hi rend="underline">thereupon promised</hi> it again within a week, &#38; <hi
                    rend="underline">now</hi>
                <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="loc.03721.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/> they (the Spr.
                Repub folks) have a <hi rend="underline">right</hi> to think I am a d&#8212;d,
                colossal &#38; continental liar<ptr
                    target="loc.03721_n4"/> (<hi rend="underline">which</hi>, en passant, I am
                    <hi rend="underline">not</hi>.)</p>
            <p>Now to the point&#8212;I <hi rend="underline">feel</hi> bound to get up that article PDQ.</p>
            <p>And I want you to go at it or let me have my <hi rend="underline">MSS</hi>. so I can get it off by next <hi
                    rend="underline">Saturday</hi> night. This is fair&#8212;&#38; I don't want to keep bothering you about it.</p>
            <p>I am hard at work at the Law&#8212;<pb xml:id="leaf004v" facs="loc.03721.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>We all enjoyed your Sunday visit&#8212;</p>
            <p>I <choice>
                    <abbr>wd</abbr>
                    <expan>would</expan>
                </choice> feel much encouraged if I <choice>
                    <abbr>cd</abbr>
                    <expan>could</expan>
                </choice> hear your gray goose quill was pointing toward Massachussetts</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Thine as ever&#8212;</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">James M Scovel</hi></signed>
            </closer>
